2 SECTION 2. IC 31-9-2-40.9 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
3 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY
4 1, 2026]: Sec. 40.9. "Discriminate", for purposes of IC 31-10-3.5,
5 includes any one (1) or more of the following acts when done solely
6 based on a person's sincerely held religious belief:
7 (1) Denying or otherwise making unavailable any funding to
8 the person, including:
9 (A) a state grant;
10 (B) a loan;
11 (C) a scholarship;
12 (D) a guarantee; or
13 (E) an entitlement or a state benefit.
14 (2) Terminating, altering the terms of, or refusing to enter
15 into a contract with the person, including a subcontract or
16 cooperative agreement.
17 (3) Refusing to recognize or taking any adverse action against
18 a person's:
19 (A) license;
20 (B) certificate;
21 (C) custody award or agreement; or
22 (D) any other similar status.
23 (4) Refusing to place a child with the person.
24 (5) Altering in any way the person's tax treatment, including:
25 (A) imposing a tax penalty;
26 (B) denying or otherwise making unavailable an exemption
27 from taxation; or
28 (C) disallowing or otherwise making unavailable a
29 deduction for state tax purposes of any charitable donation
30 made by or to the person.
31 (6) Imposing on the person any of the following:
32 (A) A monetary fine.
33 (B) A fee.
34 (C) A penalty.
35 (D) A damages award.
36 (E) An injunction.
