7 SECTION 6. IC 31-10-3.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
8 AS A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
9 JULY 1, 2026]:
10 Chapter 3.5. Antidiscrimination in Adoption and Foster
11 Proceedings
12 Sec. 1. (a) Except as provided in subsection (b), a governmental
13 entity may not discriminate against any of the following:
14 (1) A person that provides, or declines to provide, an adoption
15 or foster care service in a manner consistent with the person's
16 sincerely held religious belief.
17 (2) An adoptive parent (as defined in IC 31-9-2-6) who raises,
18 or intends to raise, a child in a manner consistent with the
19 adoptive parent's sincerely held religious belief.
20 (3) A foster parent (as defined in IC 31-9-2-47) who raises, or
21 intends to raise, a child in a manner consistent with the foster
22 parent's sincerely held religious belief.
23 (4) A person that in a matter concerning adoption or foster
24 care service:
25 (A) maintains any policy and procedure; or
26 (B) otherwise acts;
27 consistent with the person's sincerely held religious belief.
28 (b) A governmental entity may consider whether a person
29 described in subsection (a) shares the same religion or faith
30 tradition as a child when considering placement of the child to
31 prioritize the child's placement with a person of the same religion
32 or faith tradition.
33 Sec. 2. (a) Notwithstanding IC 34-13-3-3 and subject to
34 subsection (b), a person may bring a cause of action against a
35 governmental entity for a violation of section 1 of this chapter.
36 (b) A person may not bring a cause of action against any court
37 under this section.
38 (c) A person does not need to exhaust any administrative
39 remedy before commencing an action under this section.
40 Sec. 3. Relief against the governmental entity may include any
41 of the following:
42 (1) Declaratory relief.
2026 IN 1316—LS 6642/DI 148

5
1 (2) Injunctive relief.
2 (3) Compensatory damages.
3 (4) Reasonable attorney's fees and costs.
4 SECTION 7. IC 34-11-2-17 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
5 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY
6 1, 2026]: Sec. 17. An action against a governmental entity for
7 discrimination under IC 31-10-3.5-2 must be commenced not more
8 than two (2) years after the date of the act complained of.
